BIG RIVER SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Big River Solar, LLC ("Big River Solar") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Big River Solar generating facility ("Big River Solar Facility").
Big River Solar is a solar generating facility located in White County, Illinois. The Big River Solar Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Illinois Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Big River Solar' revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Big River Solar Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Big River Solar's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Big River Solar shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $650,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $54,166.67.
